			<p class="post-year">2009</p>				
		</div>

		I&#8217;ve posted my draft paper, Higher Standards: Regulation in the Network Age (Harvard Journal of Law &amp; Technology, forthcoming 2009) to the SSRN online repository.Â  Here&#8217;s the abstract: As digital networks proliferate, standardized interfaces will define the economic and normative dynamics of markets. In other words, standardization is regulation. Regulatory mechanisms must evolve to emulate the best aspects of the standard-setting process. The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) should remake itself ...
		
